    "is_author": 483302,
    "ts_title": "Brainy Babies [Arlington]",
    "ts_body": "<p>&nbsp;At Arlington Library, families enjoy stories and activities designed to encourage brain development and early learning practices [in English and Spanish]. Each week we will read books, sing songs, and do fun activities that promote language development, social-emotional skills, and more. Parents and caregivers will have the opportunity to learn about community resources and connect with peer support networks. Each week, we explore a different theme: READING, TALKING, SINGING, PLAYING, MOVEMENT, and EMOTIONS. Families will also receive FREE materials to continue the learning and fun at home.</p>",
